# .env.local.example
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to ".env.local" and fill in your wallet seeds.
#
# HOW TO GET YOUR SEEDS:
#   1. Start the dev server: npm run dev
#   2. Open your browser to: http://localhost:3000/api/setup
#   3. Copy the two seeds shown in the response
#   4. Paste them below, save, then restart the server
#
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
#   - Never commit .env.local to git (it's in .gitignore by default)
#   - These are TESTNET seeds only — they have no real monetary value
#   - On a real production app, use a proper secrets manager
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# The secret seed for Alice's wallet (the Student sending payments)
# Starts with "s", e.g. sEdTMJwFkSMTK3TrMRNgNgZsNJkSxam
STUDENT_WALLET_SEED=your_student_seed_here

# The secret seed for Bob's wallet (the Consultant receiving payments)
CONSULTANT_WALLET_SEED=your_consultant_seed_here
